      • forceUnlockIfProcessIsDead

        public boolean forceUnlockIfProcessIsDead()
        forces an unlock only if the process that currently holds the table store lock is no-longer running
        Returns:
        true if the lock was already unlocked, It will not release the lock if it is held by this process or the process that was holding the lock is no longer running (and we were able to unlock). Otherwise false is returned if the lock is held by this process or another live process.
